						<p id="american-newspapers">Throughout its existence, the USA relied on newspapers for delivering
						information to the public and to deliver to it a description of current political events. This was especially important
						during the 1800s since the American government was slowly defining itself and its practices.
						<img src="assets/charleston.jpg" style="height: 30px; width: auto;"><br>
						Newspapers were much different from the ones we have today. Rather than placing emphasis on catchphrases or using an
						eye-catching layout, they used a sober style with the objective of filling the page with as much information as possible,
						dividing the magazines in columns with the intent of making reading easier. On this point, we had to make a compromise
						between our inspiration and how articles on the web appear. Rather than dividing the text into columns and use minimal spacing, that could become so narrow it would be difficult to read articles, we opted to drop this concept. Secondly, we treated images
						 as an element that floats left, in order to make text go around them, similarly to the pictures for advertisements we can see here.
						<img src="assets/weak-men.jpg" style="height: 30px; width: auto;"><br>
						For the fonts used, we used fonts similar to the types in the National Intelligencer, the first newspaper published in the 
